# …but the wasm workspace's target rustflags (getrandom wasm_js cfg) are source:
!crates/query-wasm/.cargo/
target/
# The root Cargo.lock IS committed: this workspace ships binaries (the server
# CLI) and native bindings, and pins several git dependencies by rev. A tracked
# lock is what makes `--locked` CI builds deterministic — without it every job
# re-resolves the git deps against their branch HEAD and drifts (which is how a
# moved `delta-kernel-rs` branch previously broke CI).
integration-tests/Cargo.lock
# wasm-bindgen output of `just build-query-wasm` (a build artifact)
crates/query-wasm/pkg/

